comment_regular_data.body:
> `nvim_doc_get_lua`, `nvim_do_get_doxygen`, idk maybe more

I could see having a map of Lua and VimL, and the docstrings are optionally part of the returned metadata. Maybe then we don't need separate "doc" functions. 

Note: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/6123 is a separate discussion related to decorating user functions, though I still am not sure we need any specific function to retrieve a docstring, really we want to retrieve "function metadata" (which may be "only docstrings" initially).

```
nvim_get_viml({docstrings:true})['MyFunction'] => { 'MyFunction': { 'returntype': 'string', 'docstring': 'foo', ... }} }
nvim_get_lua({docstrings:true})['MyFunction'] => { 'MyFunction': { 'returntype': 'string', 'docstring': 'foo', ... }} }
